@Node "Introduction" "Verbes.guide/Introduction"
@Next "Menus"
@Prev "Important information"
@Toc "Main"

What is Ensemble Verbes?
************************

   Ensemble Verbes is a program to help students practise and master
French @{"verbs" Link "Verbs"} in the most common @{"tenses" Link "Tenses"} of the language.  It is designed
to *support* classroom work, not to replace it.


@EndNode

@Node "Important information" "Verbes.guide/Important information"
@Next "Introduction"
@Prev "Copyright"
@Toc "Main"

Subjects
********

   * Nous and vous are always considered plural.

   * In the passé composé, all uses of je, tu, nous and vous are
     considered masculine.

   Generic use of these pronouns will help in avoiding errors when the
subject of the pronoun is unknown.  There are also many examples with
the subjects elle, ils and elles so that the agreement of past
participles may be practised.


@EndNode

@Node "Verbs" "Verbes.guide/Verbs"
@Next "Tenses"
@Prev "Introduction"
@Toc "Introduction"

Verbs in Ensemble Verbes
************************

   Ensemble Verbes contains 76 verbs.  These verbs are split into
sections by their conjugation forms:

   * @{"-er verbs" Link "ER Verbs"}

   * @{"-ir verbs" Link "IR Verbs"}

   * @{"-re verbs" Link "RE Verbs"}

   * @{"reflexive verbs" Link "Reflexive Verbs"}

   * @{"irregular verbs" Link "Irregular Verbs"}

   These 76 verbs represent both common and uncommon conjugations in
French.  Once these verbs have been mastered, a student should have the
ability to use all French verbs.


@EndNode

